In article <60.12411.4262.0N18376D@canrem.com> terry.smith@canrem.com (Terry
Smith) writes:
>I *BELEIVE* this is a way to safely confirm a secret key over an insecure
>channel.
>
>Create a *random* bit string the length of the key
>XOR it with the key
>Send THAT over the channel
>The other guy XORs it with the key (Which shoiuld be the same as YOUR key)
>and sends it back
>You check and if it's the RANDOM STRING - he's in!
>
>The eavesdropper is left with a random string...

No, the eavesdropper is left with two strings, one sent in each direction, and
their XOR is the secret key.

Rujith de Silva.
